structure.unit: COUNTIES, CITIES, AND OTHER LOCAL UNITS
COUNTY GOVERNMENT (FISCAL COURTS AND COUNTY COMMISSIONERS)

text.section: Any officer who willfully violates any of the provisions of KRS 67.020 is guilty of misfeasance in office, and shall be fined not more than one hundred dollars ($100).
Any officer who willfully violates any of the provisions of KRS 67.090(2) shall be fined not less than fifty dollars ($50) nor more than two hundred dollars ($200) for each offense.

law.history: Amended 1980 Ky. Acts ch. 188, sec. 45, effective July 15, 1980. -- Amended 1968 Ky. Acts ch. 152, sec. 37. -- Amended 1954 Ky. Acts ch. 25, sec. 4. -- Recodified 1942 Ky. Acts ch. 208, sec. 1, effective October 1, 1942, from Ky. Stat. secs. 918, 928h-58.
